xxl.core.cursors

Class AbstractMetaDataCursor<E,M>

  • java.lang.Object
    • xxl.core.cursors.SecureDecoratorCursor<E>
      • xxl.core.cursors.AbstractMetaDataCursor<E,M>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of the elements returned by this cursor.
    M - the type of the given meta data object.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterator<E>, Cursor<E>, MetaDataCursor<E,M>, MetaDataProvider<M>

    public abstract class AbstractMetaDataCursor<E,M>
extends SecureDecoratorCursor<E>
implements MetaDataCursor<E,M>
    This class decorates an object implementing the interface Cursor such that it is able to provide metadata information. For this reason this class extends the class SecureDecoratorCursor by additionally implementing the interface MetaDataProvider. For getting a concrete instance of this abstract class the method getMetaData has to be overwritten such that it returns the metadata information for the decorated cursor.

    Note: When the given input iteration only implements the interface Iterator it is wrapped to a cursor by a call to the static method wrap.

    See Also:
    Iterator, Cursor, SecureDecoratorCursor

      • AbstractMetaDataCursor

        public AbstractMetaDataCursor(Iterator<E> iterator)
        Creates a new abstract metadata-cursor. The given iteration is wrapped to a cursor by calling the method Cursors.wrap(java.util.Iterator) and decorated such that solely the abstract method getMetaData has to be overwritten for getting a cursor that is able to provide its meta data information.
        Parameters:
        iterator - the iterator to be decorated.
